const keyTakeaways = [
  'Complete decision framework with scoring system',
  'Real-world testing methodology and results',
  'Cost analysis including hidden expenses',
  'Common mistakes that cost businesses thousands',
];

const faqItems = [
  {
    question: 'What is the best AI chatbot for beginners?',
    answer: 'For beginners, Google Gemini (formerly Bard) and ChatGPT are the top choices. Both offer free tiers, intuitive interfaces, and broad capability. ChatGPT excels at creative tasks and coding, while Gemini integrates deeply with Google Search for real-time information. Start with either one and explore before committing to a paid plan.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is ChatGPT better than Claude for most tasks?',
    answer: 'It depends on the task. ChatGPT (GPT-4o) is generally better for coding, math, and image generation. Claude (Anthropic) outperforms ChatGPT on long-document analysis, nuanced writing, and following complex instructions. For everyday use they are very comparable. See our full ChatGPT vs Claude vs Bard comparison for details.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the difference between free and paid AI chatbots?',
    answer: 'Free tiers provide limited access to older or smaller models, with usage caps and no priority access during peak hours. Paid plans (typically $20/month) unlock the latest flagship models (GPT-4o, Claude 3 Opus, Gemini Advanced), higher message limits, image generation, file uploads, and faster response times. For occasional use, free tiers are sufficient. For daily professional use, paid plans deliver dramatically better results.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Which AI chatbot has the best free tier?',
    answer: 'Google Gemini offers the most generous free tier in 2025 — access to Gemini Pro with no daily message cap for standard queries, plus real-time web search. Perplexity AI is a close second with free AI-powered search and citations. ChatGPT Free (GPT-4o mini) and Claude Free (Claude 3 Haiku) are also strong options with different strengths.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I evaluate an AI chatbot before committing?',
    answer: 'Use this 5-step evaluation: (1) Test with your real use cases — not just generic prompts. (2) Check accuracy on facts relevant to your field. (3) Evaluate response consistency across 10+ similar queries. (4) Test edge cases and refusals. (5) Assess context retention over a long conversation. Most platforms offer free trials or free tiers sufficient for evaluation.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What AI chatbot is best for coding?',
    answer: 'GitHub Copilot (powered by GPT-4o) is the gold standard for in-IDE code assistance. For chatbot-style coding help, ChatGPT Plus and Claude Pro are the top contenders. ChatGPT tends to produce more immediately runnable code; Claude excels at explaining and refactoring large codebases. For free coding assistance, the free tiers of both work well for common languages.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Which AI chatbot is best for content writing?',
    answer: 'Claude (Anthropic) consistently produces the most natural-sounding, nuanced long-form writing. ChatGPT is excellent for structured content like blog posts, emails, and product descriptions. For SEO-focused content, tools built on GPT-4 like Jasper or Copy.ai add workflow features. For most writers, the free tier of either Claude or ChatGPT is a great starting point.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Are AI chatbots safe to use for sensitive information?',
    answer: 'Exercise caution with sensitive data. Most AI chatbots (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini) log conversations by default and may use them to improve their models. Never share passwords, financial account details, personal health information, or confidential business data. Use the opt-out settings available in each platform, or choose privacy-focused alternatives like DuckDuckGo AI Chat or Mistral. For enterprise use, look for SOC 2-certified platforms with data processing agreements.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can AI chatbots remember previous conversations?',
    answer: 'Memory varies by platform. ChatGPT Plus has a persistent memory feature you can manage. Claude currently remembers context only within a single conversation (no cross-session memory by default). Gemini has Google integration that can optionally sync with your history. Most free tiers have no long-term memory. For business use, custom integrations or tools like Mem.ai can provide persistent context across sessions.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the most accurate AI chatbot in 2025?',
    answer: 'Accuracy depends on the domain. For factual, cited answers, Perplexity AI is the most reliable because it searches the web in real-time and cites sources. For reasoning and logic, GPT-4o and Claude 3 Opus score highest on benchmarks. For STEM tasks, GPT-4o and Gemini Ultra lead. For creative and analytical tasks, Claude 3 Opus is often the most accurate. Always verify important facts regardless of the platform.',
  },
];
